      "src/delivery/services/DeliveryService.ts — add event publishing on status transitions",
      "src/notifications/worker.ts — queue consumer entry point, pulls from SQS",
      "src/notifications/router/NotificationRouter.ts — resolves preferences, renders templates, fans out to dispatchers",
      "src/notifications/dispatchers/Dispatcher.ts — common interface: dispatch(recipient, message) → Result",
      "src/notifications/dispatchers/EmailDispatcher.ts — SendGrid adapter",
      "src/notifications/dispatchers/SmsDispatcher.ts — Twilio adapter",
      "src/notifications/templates/ — message templates per status per channel",
      "src/notifications/idempotency/IdempotencyStore.ts — dedup check using eventId + channel",
      "infrastructure/sqs.tf (or CDK/CloudFormation) — queue, DLQ, retry policy, alarm"
    ],
    "patterns_to_follow": "Use a Dispatcher interface with dispatch(recipient: Recipient, message: RenderedMessage): Promise<DispatchResult> where DispatchResult = Success | TransientFailure(reason) | PermanentFailure(reason). The router handles TransientFailure by letting the message return to the queue (throw and let visibility timeout re-deliver). PermanentFailure is logged and the message is acknowledged (acked) to prevent infinite retry of unrecoverable errors (e.g., invalid phone number). Keep the worker as a single deployable unit — do not over-distribute for a 3-person team.",
    "pitfalls_to_avoid": [
      "Do NOT build a custom retry mechanism — use the queue's native retry + DLQ. Hand-rolled retry loops are a common source of bugs.",
      "Do NOT make the delivery service wait for notification success — publish the event and move on. The whole point is decoupling.",
      "Do NOT use a FIFO queue unless you have a specific ordering requirement — standard queues have higher throughput and simpler semantics.",
      "Do NOT deploy each dispatcher as a separate microservice — for a 3-person team this creates unnecessary operational overhead. Keep them as modules in one worker.",
      "Do NOT skip the idempotency check — 'it probably won't send duplicates' is how customers get 5 identical SMS messages.",
      "Do NOT forget schema versioning on domain events — add a version field now, even if you only have v1. Future you will thank present you."
    ]
  },

